<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The comments above would indicate that this spell is not so powerful (doing only 75pts).  In fact, the rain effect lasts 2 tics so it actually does 75pts to all targets twice (total of 150pts) as long as they stay inside the effect.<BR>
<BR>
:D</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Pumukl Drachenodem</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-13 09:37:15</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>you are not really exact ;-) <BR>
Lightning storm hits 3 times for each 75 dmg, but will mostly resisted min. 1 time. Your max. dmg will be 225dmg and you can cast another DD spell during rain. Be careful to cast first root then storm and then Frost shock. after each spell (During recovery) move a little farther away, from far you can cast lightning bolt (Only outside!), and if root then leaves cast it again ;-) Soloing will be much easier so ;-)<BR>
Many greetings<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
