<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Ivythorne</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2001-03-11 02:18:37</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I'm a druid, so I'm not sure if it works the same for Wizard spells, but when it says Lightning in the spell title, it means its Magic based...Fire/Flame/Ignite in the title means fire based...Sicken/disease/pox in title = disease...poison/taint in title = poison....rain reference *such as Pogonip*/ice/frost/hail in title = cold based. Hope that helps some. I would be willing to bet this is magic based. Which sucks for those monks who use the staff with this proc, because it will hit them too, and they probably won't have enough MR to resist it heheh.... oh well.  Like I said, hope that helps.</font></td></tr></table>
